THE GAME
--------

  'IsoGate' is a Workbench game where you have to move an 'X'
shape from its position at the upper left to the exit, which is
represented by a small box and is located at the lower right of
the game board.

  To move the X shape, it must be surrounded by gates and/or one
or more of the game boards edges, so there is only one opening
where the X shape can go. The gates are moved using the arrows
located around the game board.

  To complicate matters a little bit, there are two things to keep
in mind: some gates have a limit of travel. Another complication
is that as you move on a game board, one or more gates can move
randomly...

  Complete each game board in the least amount of moves.

  Have fun!

